  "text": "Boundary condition of 3D Argyris FEM space. The enhanced continuities are imposed on the edge and vertex for the 3D Argris finite element. Therefore, we follow the terminology in [CITATION_1] to introduce the corner vertices and corner edges. For a corner boundary vertex in 3D, there are three linearly independent boundary edges connected to it. Hence, all the degrees of freedom at the corner boundary vertex should be set to zero. Similarly, on a corner edge, derivatives of a function along two normal directions can be determined by the function value on the boundary. Hence, all the degrees of freedom at the corner boundary vertex should be set to zero.",
